  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nHost system is Linux Mint 18.1 x64.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nI'm writing a Dockerfile that uses `ethereum/client-go` as the base image. That's supposed to be running Ubuntu.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\nWelcome to Alpine Linux 3.8\r\nKernel \\r on an \\m (\\l)\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nDockerfile:\r\n\r\n```\r\nFROM ethereum/client-go\r\nRUN cat /etc/issue\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun:\r\n```\r\ndocker build - < Dockerfile\r\n```\r\n\r\nNB: If I use `ethereum/client-go:alpine`, I also get an Alpine-based system.\r\n",
